## BROWSER RELIABILITY RULE (Critical)
When performing browser automation, prefer resilient commands over direct clicks.

Required behavior:
1. Before heavy browser actions, run `openclaw-browser-heal --max-tabs 6`.
2. For click actions, prefer `openclaw-browser-safe-click <ref> 6 5 1 15000`.
3. If safe-click still fails, run `openclaw browser snapshot --limit 100`, re-resolve the target ref, then retry once.
4. If browser tools become slow/unavailable, run `openclaw-browser-heal` immediately and continue.

Never assume page refs are stable on X; always be ready to re-snapshot and re-target.

START-ACTION GUARANTEE:
- Never say "starting X work" (or equivalent) unless at least one real browser action has completed successfully in this turn (for example: open, focus, navigate, click).
- Immediately after the first successful action, report one observable fact (URL opened, tab id, or page title) so progress is verifiable.
- If browser is not running, say so explicitly and run recovery first (`openclaw-browser-heal --max-tabs 6`).

X CURATION RULE:
- For all X curation/follow tasks, follow the procedures in `TOOLS.md` under **X Curation Procedure**.
- Final line of every curation batch: `attempted=<n> succeeded=<n> failed=<n> before=<n|unknown> after=<n|unknown> follow_delta=<n|unknown>`. Do not use `delta=`, only `follow_delta=`.
- Confirmation once authorizes a bounded batch (default: 5 handles or 10 min). Do not ask again unless scope changes.
- Treat each turn as one bounded execution unit. State the exact blocker and next recovery step if the run stops early.

AUTH FAILURE RULE:
- If any model call returns `401 unauthorized` or `token expired`, stop normal task flow and report auth failure immediately.
- Provide the exact recovery command: `openclaw models auth login-github-copilot`.
- After auth succeeds, resume the pending task from the last confirmed checkpoint instead of restarting from scratch.
- Never present auth-failed turns as task progress.

NO-SILENT-END RULE:
- Do not finish actionable turns with empty output.
- Before ending a turn, always emit a concise textual completion line with either:
   - result summary (what was done, observable fact), or
   - blocker summary (exact blocker + next command).
- Never call or rely on an empty `end_turn` style completion for actionable work.
- If a tool/action completed but no user-facing text has been produced yet, write the summary text first, then end the turn.

